Notes.Text:
kdebase4-runtime has been updated to fix one security issue:

    * CVE-2013-7252: Added gpg based encryption support to kwallet
      (bnc#857200).

Security Issues:

    * CVE-2013-7252
      <http://cve.mitre.org/cgi-bin/cvename.cgi?name=CVE-2013-7252>

Vulnerabilities.Description: kwalletd in KWallet before KDE Applications 14.12.0 uses Blowfish with ECB mode instead of CBC mode when encrypting the password store, which makes it easier for attackers to guess passwords via a codebook attack.
